  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence is drawn from a comprehensive observational study of clinical pump performance data across multiple institutions, which the assessment narrative characterises as providing experimental-grade corroboration of CFD hemolysis predictions. The study tracked RH index values across 47 patient-pump pairings under routine CPB flow conditions, and the breadth of the dataset is cited as functionally equivalent to a controlled bench experiment. However, the governing Requirement for this COU mandates a controlled-experiment verification method; the supporting ValidationResult was generated by an observational-study activity, creating an inference-method mismatch that is not surfaced in the narrative.",
