      "name": "Relative Hemolysis Index Validation — Multi-Institution Observational Cohort",
      "description": "Predicted RH index values from the CFD model were compared against RH index measurements drawn from a 47-patient multi-institution observational cohort study conducted under routine CPB flow conditions (2.0–5.5 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM). Agreement across all five target flow-speed combinations was within 8% of measured mean RH values, with RH < 1 satisfied in 44 of 47 cases. The breadth of real-world operating conditions sampled in the cohort is described in the assessment narrative as providing experimental-grade corroboration functionally equivalent to controlled bench testing. Mean bias was 0.04 RH units (95% CI: −0.11 to +0.19).",
      "quantitativeResult": "Mean RH bias = 0.04; 95% CI [-0.11, +0.19]; 44/47 cases satisfy RH < 1",
